body:
> Can you attach an example that shows the issue?

Example:

```verilog
module sv_rand_stability;

    initial begin

        process p; string s;
        p = process::self();

        $display("%8h", $urandom());
        $display("%8h", $urandom());
        if($test$plusargs("save_randstate")) begin
            s = p.get_randstate();
        end
        $display("%8h", $urandom());
        $display("%8h", $urandom());

        $finish();

    end

endmodule
```

Outputs with and without `+save_randstate` must be the same. `get_randstate()` must not change process RNG. Tested with big-3.

> What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```bash
verilator --binary ./sv_rand_stability.sv
./obj_dir/Vsv_rand_stability +verilator+seed+12345
./obj_dir/Vsv_rand_stability +verilator+seed+12345 +save_randstate
```

> What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

`Verilator 5.035 devel rev v5.034-69-g780163b91`

> What OS and distribution are you using?

CentOS Linux release 7.9.2009.

